}
@media (max-width: 768px) { .games-title { font-size: 2.1rem; } .games-stats { gap: 1.5rem; } }
</style>

<div class="games-page">
  <div class="games-inner">
    <header class="games-hero">
      <span class="games-eyebrow">Chess School &middot; Library</span>
      <h1 class="games-title">Our Games Library</h1>
      <p class="games-sub">Almost 15 million chess games &mdash; from the oldest games ever recorded to last week's grandmaster tournaments &mdash; collected, organized, and ready to play through on the board. Pick a game, click it, and watch the moves unfold. No download, no signup, no leaving the page.</p>
      <div class="games-stats">
        <div class="games-stat"><span class="games-stat-num">14.8M</span><span class="games-stat-label">Games</span></div>
        <div class="games-stat"><span class="games-stat-num">540 yrs</span><span class="games-stat-label">Of history</span></div>
        <div class="games-stat"><span class="games-stat-num">500+</span><span class="games-stat-label">Openings</span></div>
        <div class="games-stat"><span class="games-stat-num">36</span><span class="games-stat-label">Great players</span></div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <!-- ChessBase-style hierarchical opening tree.
         Each leaf code is a .game-card.eco-card so it picks up the same
         click handler as the tab grids and opens the viewer. -->
    <details class="tree-section" open>
      <summary>Opening Tree &mdash; how the codes group together</summary>
      <div class="tree-body">
        <p class="tree-intro">
          <strong>Every chess opening lives somewhere in this tree.</strong> Long ago, the world's chess teachers carved every possible first move into a few big families &mdash; flank openings, semi-open games, open games, closed games, Indian defenses. Each family was given a letter (A through E) and a number (00 through 99). Click any branch to open it; click any code at the bottom to play through the games inside.
        </p>

        {ecoTree.map((bucket) => (
          <details class="tree-node">
            <summary set:html={bucket.label}></summary>
            {bucket.help && <div class="tree-help" set:html={bucket.help}></div>}
            {bucket.children ? (
              bucket.children.map((sub) => (
                <details class="tree-subnode">
                  <summary set:html={sub.label}></summary>
                  <div class="tree-leaves">
                    {(sub.codes || []).map((code) => {
                      const entry = ecoByCode.get(code);
                      if (!entry) return null;
                      return (
                        <div class="tree-leaf game-card eco-card" data-search={(code + ' ' + entry.name).toLowerCase()} data-file={`eco/${code}.pgn`} data-label={`ECO ${code} — ${entry.name}`} data-bytes={entry.bytes} role="button" tabindex="0">
                          <span class="tree-leaf-code">{code}</span>
                          <span class="tree-leaf-name">{entry.name}</span>
                          <span class="tree-leaf-count">{fmtCount(entry.games)}</span>
                        </div>
                      );
                    })}
                  </div>
                </details>
              ))
            ) : (
              <div class="tree-leaves">
                {(bucket.codes || []).map((code) => {
                  const entry = ecoByCode.get(code);
                  if (!entry) return null;
                  return (
                    <div class="tree-leaf game-card eco-card" data-search={(code + ' ' + entry.name).toLowerCase()} data-file={`eco/${code}.pgn`} data-label={`ECO ${code} — ${entry.name}`} data-bytes={entry.bytes} role="button" tabindex="0">
                      <span class="tree-leaf-code">{code}</span>
                      <span class="tree-leaf-name">{entry.name}</span>
                      <span class="tree-leaf-count">{fmtCount(entry.games)}</span>
                    </div>
                  );
                })}
              </div>
            )}
          </details>
        ))}
      </div>
    </details>

    <nav class="tab-bar" role="tablist">
      <button class="tab-btn active" data-tab="eco" role="tab">By Opening (Modern)</button>
      <button class="tab-btn" data-tab="historical" role="tab">By Opening (Historical)</button>
      <button class="tab-btn" data-tab="players" role="tab">By Player</button>
      <button class="tab-btn" data-tab="events" role="tab">By Tournament</button>
      <button class="tab-btn" data-tab="openings" role="tab">By Opening Name</button>
    </nav>

    <section class="tab-panel active" data-panel="eco">
      <div class="panel-intro">
        <strong>Modern tournament games &mdash; the last fourteen years.</strong> Every game here was played at a serious chess tournament somewhere in the world since 2012, gathered into our library week by week.
        <br><br>
        They're sorted by <strong>opening code</strong>. Long ago, chess teachers grouped the thousands of ways to start a game into <strong>five families</strong>, labeled A through E, with numbers from 00 to 99 inside each family. So a Sicilian Defense (a famous Black response to 1.e4) sits in family B; the Queen's Gambit lives in family D. Pick any code below to open the door to that family of games.
      </div>
      <div class="search-row">
        <input type="text" class="search-input" id="eco-search" placeholder="Search ECO code or opening name (e.g. B90, Najdorf, Reti)..." aria-label="Search ECO" />
        <span class="search-info">{ecoEntries.length} ECO codes &middot; {fmtCount(totalEcoGames)} games</span>
      </div>
      <div class="games-grid" id="eco-grid">
        {ecoEntries.length === 0 ? (
          <div class="empty">Manifest unavailable at build time. Refresh after the next deploy.</div>
        ) : ecoEntries.map((e) => (
          <div class="game-card eco-card" data-search={(e.code + ' ' + e.name).toLowerCase()} data-file={`eco/${e.code}.pgn`} data-label={`ECO ${e.code} — ${e.name}`} data-bytes={e.bytes} role="button" tabindex="0">
            <div class="game-card-head">
              <span class="game-card-code">{e.code}</span>
              <span class="game-card-size">{bytesToHuman(e.bytes)}</span>
            </div>
            <div class="game-card-name">{e.name}</div>
            <div class="game-card-stats">{fmtCount(e.games)} games</div>
            <span class="game-card-cta">&#9654; Browse Games</span>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="tab-panel" data-panel="historical">
      <div class="panel-intro">
        <strong>The Long Memory &mdash; every game we have, going back five hundred and forty years.</strong> The oldest game in here was played in 1485, when Christopher Columbus hadn't yet crossed the Atlantic. The newest was played this past week. Eleven million games sit between those two moments.
        <br><br>
        Like the tab before, the games are grouped by the same A&ndash;E opening codes. Open any door and you'll find masters and amateurs across five centuries, all reaching for the same first move.
      </div>
      <div class="search-row">
        <input type="text" class="search-input" id="hist-search" placeholder="Search ECO code or opening name..." aria-label="Search historical ECO" />
        <span class="search-info">{histEntries.length} ECO codes &middot; {fmtCount(totalHistGames)} games</span>
      </div>
      <div class="games-grid" id="hist-grid">
        {histEntries.length === 0 ? (
          <div class="empty">Manifest unavailable at build time. Refresh after the next deploy.</div>
        ) : histEntries.map((e) => (
          <div class="game-card eco-card" data-search={(e.code + ' ' + e.name).toLowerCase()} data-file={`historical/${e.code}.pgn`} data-label={`${e.code} — ${e.name}`} data-bytes={e.bytes} role="button" tabindex="0">
            <div class="game-card-head">
              <span class="game-card-code">{e.code}</span>
              <span class="game-card-size">{bytesToHuman(e.bytes)}</span>
            </div>
            <div class="game-card-name">{e.name}</div>
            <div class="game-card-stats">{fmtCount(e.games)} games</div>
            <span class="game-card-cta">&#9654; Browse Games</span>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="tab-panel" data-panel="players">
      <div class="panel-intro">
        <strong>Thirty-six of the greatest chess players who ever lived.</strong> Every published game by each of them, in one place. Modern champions are at the top of the page; the old masters &mdash; from Paul Morphy to Mikhail Tal &mdash; are right below.
        <br><br>
        Click any name to open a player's library, then click a game to watch it move by move.
      </div>
      <div class="search-row">
        <input type="text" class="search-input" id="player-search" placeholder="Search by name (e.g. Carlsen, Fischer, Polgar)..." aria-label="Search player" />
        <span class="search-info">{playersModern.length + playersClassical.length} players</span>
      </div>

      <h3 style="font-family:'Playfair Display',Georgia,serif; color:var(--gold); margin:1.5rem 0 1rem; font-size:1.2rem; letter-spacing:0.05em;">Champions of Today</h3>
      <div class="games-grid">
        {playersModern.map((p) => (
          <div class="game-card player-card" data-name={p.name.toLowerCase()} data-file={`players/${p.file}.pgn`} data-label={p.name} role="button" tabindex="0">
